Well, we can start a class right here today
I suppose,

00:24:00.420 --> 00:24:03.160
but I don't want to keep everybody from their
roller

00:24:03.160 --> 00:24:06.300
skating or whatever it is they're out there
--

00:24:06.300 --> 00:24:08.200
[Laughing]
&gt;&gt;DORIS: I expect we're going to have a lot

00:24:08.200 --> 00:24:09.200
of
fun.

00:24:09.200 --> 00:24:11.080
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Yes.
&gt;&gt;DORIS: And we're going to be terribly proud

00:24:11.080 --> 00:24:13.980
of the product. And just imagine setting all
those

00:24:13.980 --> 00:24:16.660
people out to do whatever they're going to
do in their

00:24:16.660 --> 00:24:19.221
lives. As I say, it may not be for 30 years,
but they

00:24:19.221 --> 00:24:22.890
will know how to do it, and they won't get
fleeced, and

00:24:22.890 --> 00:24:27.330
that's very important to me. We're both doing
our thing

00:24:27.330 --> 00:24:31.390
in our own way, but I think I'm probably getting
more

00:24:31.390 --> 00:24:34.800
fun out of it than just turning it over to
-- you know.

00:24:34.800 --> 00:24:37.730
I'm not speaking of the living -- Learning
by Giving,

00:24:37.730 --> 00:24:40.870
I'm just talking in general. All the proposals
that

00:24:40.870 --> 00:24:43.220
come my way.
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Oh, sure. And if someone wanted

00:24:43.220 --> 00:24:45.809
to
get a proposal to you, or if we had friends

00:24:45.809 --> 00:24:47.960
that -- how
would we go about doing that?

00:24:47.960 --> 00:24:53.660
&gt;&gt;DORIS: Well, you just send it to our office,
and just look at our web site, okay --

00:24:53.660 --> 00:24:58.050
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Look at you promoting the Internet.
[Laughing]

00:24:58.050 --> 00:25:01.480
&gt;&gt;DORIS: I'm so proud of myself.
[Laughing]

00:25:01.480 --> 00:25:08.820
&gt;&gt;DORIS: And they'll get all the information
they need, and we will take it under consideration.

00:25:08.820 --> 00:25:13.370
And
it's really a pleasure being here. Just a

00:25:13.370 --> 00:25:16.180
tremendous
pleasure. I'm going to leave here with one

00:25:16.180 --> 00:25:18.750
of those --
what do you call it? Scooters.

00:25:18.750 --> 00:25:21.870
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Yes.
&gt;&gt;DORIS: No. I'll have to steal it I guess.

00:25:21.870 --> 00:25:23.740
[Laughing]
&gt;&gt;DORIS: That wouldn't be a good example at

00:25:23.740 --> 00:25:27.880
all, but I think that's so clever.
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Trust me, it comes in very handy.

00:25:27.880 --> 00:25:31.110
&gt;&gt;DORIS: I'm sure it does. You're in a hurry.
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Exactly. Or there's a really long

00:25:31.110 --> 00:25:34.679
floor to try to get across to.
&gt;&gt;DORIS: Yeah! This building's enormous.

00:25:34.679 --> 00:25:36.750
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: It is. It's a rather large
footprint here for--.

00:25:36.750 --> 00:25:42.090
&gt;&gt;DORIS: Well, you've got a great thing here,
an amazing thing. We're glad to be associated

00:25:42.090 --> 00:25:45.660
with you,
just tickled to death because that just -- imagine

00:25:45.660 --> 00:25:48.350
how
that expands the kind of work you can do.

00:25:48.350 --> 00:25:49.510
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Absolutely.
&gt;&gt;DORIS: It's wonderful.

00:25:49.510 --> 00:25:52.679
&gt;&gt;Female#1: We have a question here
&gt;&gt;Female #2: Hi, Doris . I'm just wondering

00:25:52.679 --> 00:25:55.080
if you can
share the story of the person you helped that

00:25:55.080 --> 00:25:57.940
touched
you the most.

00:25:57.940 --> 00:26:05.840
&gt;&gt;DORIS: Oh, my gosh. Oh. Well... uh, first
of all, when we're doing individual things,

00:26:05.840 --> 00:26:08.299
we do people
who have bad luck, not people who have made

00:26:08.299 --> 00:26:14.100
wrong
choices because it bothers you for sort of

00:26:14.100 --> 00:26:16.360
paying them
off for making a dumb decision. I've made

00:26:16.360 --> 00:26:20.360
some, so I
can refer to it that way. So I'll just take

00:26:20.360 --> 00:26:23.280
the most
recent one because I don't, there are hundreds

00:26:23.280 --> 00:26:27.020
and
hundreds of them now, I'm telling you. Umm...

00:26:27.020 --> 00:26:31.780
I got two
recently and -- just the other day. One was

00:26:31.780 --> 00:26:34.500
a -- I have
a crew up in Maine that handles individual

00:26:34.500 --> 00:26:39.580
cases, and my
brother pays for that part, so he's involved.

00:26:39.580 --> 00:26:44.440
And this
woman had written in and I can't remember

00:26:44.440 --> 00:26:47.770
the illness
she had because we were in the mall, but she

00:26:47.770 --> 00:26:52.100
had a
motorized wheelchair and to get to the bus

00:26:52.100 --> 00:26:57.020
stop she had
to go a mile, and whether snow, sleet, rain,

00:26:57.020 --> 00:27:00.090
mud, the
whole thing, and I don't even remember her

00:27:00.090 --> 00:27:03.140
illness, but
I'll tell you, MS is a big illness in this

00:27:03.140 --> 00:27:06.040
country today
because we've helped more people that have

00:27:06.040 --> 00:27:10.070
MS than I can
imagine. So she needed a van, something that

00:27:10.070 --> 00:27:11.850
would
handle the wheelchair and get her where she

00:27:11.850 --> 00:27:15.760
was going.
So our rule up in Maine is if it comes in

00:27:15.760 --> 00:27:18.550
at 5,000 or
less they can go ahead and use their own judgment

00:27:18.550 --> 00:27:22.220
because they're all smart and they're in the
-- in the

00:27:22.220 --> 00:27:24.730
deal. They understand it. So this would take
a little

00:27:24.730 --> 00:27:26.640
more. We never buy new ones; we always buy
used ones,

00:27:26.640 --> 00:27:29.490
but we know every used van dealer in the country.
[Laughing]

00:27:29.490 --> 00:27:36.101
&gt;&gt;DORIS: They are so knowledgeable up there.
And so I said, well, go ahead. And then a

00:27:36.101 --> 00:27:39.000
few days
later, the girl who was handling the program

00:27:39.000 --> 00:27:41.640
called me
what she said -- it was just amazing. She

00:27:41.640 --> 00:27:43.880
called the
lady back and said she was going to get her

00:27:43.880 --> 00:27:47.179
van, when
she said there was this long silence and then

00:27:47.179 --> 00:27:51.860
uncontrollable weeping. And it just made all
the -- and

00:27:51.860 --> 00:27:53.890
it was -- once again, it gets back to the
thing about

00:27:53.890 --> 00:27:57.280
having a personal connection. It wasn't just
the van;

00:27:57.280 --> 00:28:00.460
she made that clear. It was the fact that
someone,

00:28:00.460 --> 00:28:05.221
somewhere, recognized her and wanted to help
her. These

00:28:05.221 --> 00:28:08.980
are invisible people in many cases, and as
these legions

00:28:08.980 --> 00:28:12.280
go forth from these programs, think how many
more we can

00:28:12.280 --> 00:28:17.890
help with that. That happens oh, gosh, I can't
-- oh,

00:28:17.890 --> 00:28:21.049
and then another thing we stress is paying
it forward

00:28:21.049 --> 00:28:25.250
in every one. I was up in Maine a year ago
and the

00:28:25.250 --> 00:28:27.750
phone rang, and a woman called -- said, my
name is

00:28:27.750 --> 00:28:29.810
Susan. I can't remember her last name. She
said, you

00:28:29.810 --> 00:28:32.860
saved our family a year ago. She said, we
still don't

00:28:32.860 --> 00:28:36.500
have much money, but I have collected over
4,000 pairs

00:28:36.500 --> 00:28:40.150
of shoes and they're going to Haiti. Now,
I love that

00:28:40.150 --> 00:28:44.370
story; that's true. And it shows it's a catching
thing.

00:28:44.370 --> 00:28:50.860
If you do it on a very kindly, caring, reasonable
basis,

00:28:50.860 --> 00:28:53.840
and it isn't as they say a handout -- that's
money

00:28:53.840 --> 00:28:57.480
wasted. So that's going on all over the country
and

00:28:57.480 --> 00:29:01.870
when we turn this group loose, I mean really,
it's going

00:29:01.870 --> 00:29:05.280
to be monumental.
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Another question here.

00:29:05.280 --> 00:29:08.820
&gt;&gt;Female #3: Thank you so much for coming
today. One

00:29:08.820 --> 00:29:13.950
of the questions I had was you make the distinction
between those who've had poor luck and poor

00:29:13.950 --> 00:29:16.700
circumstance, and those who've possibly made
bad

00:29:16.700 --> 00:29:19.530
choices. Those so often go hand in hand that
bad

00:29:19.530 --> 00:29:21.651
circumstances often lead to bad choices, and
I was

00:29:21.651 --> 00:29:23.970
wondering how your organization makes the
distinction.

00:29:23.970 --> 00:29:29.230
I'm sure it's a many-layered question, but--
&gt;&gt;DORIS: It's a many-layered answer, too,

00:29:29.230 --> 00:29:32.540
as a
matter of fact. In some cases, yes, you can

00:29:32.540 --> 00:29:35.690
see it, but
you try to balance it out. But other cases

00:29:35.690 --> 00:29:39.960
are so
unmistakably bad luck. Nobody did anything

00:29:39.960 --> 00:29:41.170
wrong. Can
I tell one more?

00:29:41.170 --> 00:29:45.240
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Of course.
&gt;&gt;DORIS: Okay. I got a letter from a woman,

00:29:45.240 --> 00:29:48.370
a
nurse, she was a nurse by occupation, lived

00:29:48.370 --> 00:29:52.760
in Arapaho,
Colorado, and she had a twin sister who lived

00:29:52.760 --> 00:29:56.600
in
Memphis, Tennessee. Both of these sisters,

00:29:56.600 --> 00:30:01.919
twins, had
girls the same age, ten years old, so nothing

00:30:01.919 --> 00:30:06.370
followed
this. So the ten-year-old from Memphis, Tennessee,

00:30:06.370 --> 00:30:08.750
probably got on a gray hound bus and went
to visit her

00:30:08.750 --> 00:30:12.780
cousin of the same age on a cool Colorado
one summer,

00:30:12.780 --> 00:30:16.030
and presumably had a wonderful time, and then
she went

00:30:16.030 --> 00:30:19.650
back home. Now, her mother in Tennessee was
divorced

00:30:19.650 --> 00:30:23.840
and she was working two jobs, and keeping
her children

00:30:23.840 --> 00:30:27.340
going and so on. She had no health insurance,
of

00:30:27.340 --> 00:30:30.040
course. And when this little girl got back
there, she

00:30:30.040 --> 00:30:33.030
had a spot under her left eye, and it didn't
seem to go

00:30:33.030 --> 00:30:36.760
away so her mother took her to a hospital,
the emergency

00:30:36.760 --> 00:30:39.990
room, and they gave her Noxema or something
and sent

00:30:39.990 --> 00:30:42.940
them home. Then they went back a second time
a few

00:30:42.940 --> 00:30:45.160
weeks later because it wasn't having any effect
on this

00:30:45.160 --> 00:30:48.420
place, and then the third time they went in,
they saw a

00:30:48.420 --> 00:30:50.970
doctor, and he did a biopsy and sent it off
to some

00:30:50.970 --> 00:30:57.240
really good places. When it came back, she
had a

00:30:57.240 --> 00:31:01.799
disease -- what is that? What do you call
that? It's

00:31:01.799 --> 00:31:04.940
creepy kind of thing. What is it in fungus.
Yeah. It

00:31:04.940 --> 00:31:10.750
was a fungal infection or condition, and there
were two

00:31:10.750 --> 00:31:13.429
people in this country that had it and 43
that had it in

00:31:13.429 --> 00:31:18.721
Bangladesh. I mean, it's just -- how would
you ever get

00:31:18.721 --> 00:31:21.600
that? She went on the bus, she had a good
time, she

00:31:21.600 --> 00:31:25.160
came home on the bus, and now by time I heard
from them,

00:31:25.160 --> 00:31:28.330
I then contacted the mother, and she was at
that point

00:31:28.330 --> 00:31:31.680
working nights so she could be with her daughter
in the

00:31:31.680 --> 00:31:33.980
daytime in the hospital, and the girl had
been in

00:31:33.980 --> 00:31:36.809
intensive care at different times, and it
was spreading,

00:31:36.809 --> 00:31:40.450
and she was blind in one eye. And she could
go home for

00:31:40.450 --> 00:31:42.679
a while, but she was terrified to go home
for fear her

00:31:42.679 --> 00:31:44.610
friends would make fun of her, you know, because
her

00:31:44.610 --> 00:31:48.020
face was mixed up. So we were able -- the
woman sounded

00:31:48.020 --> 00:31:51.610
like death warmed over and so I said how are
you getting

00:31:51.610 --> 00:31:53.900
along financially? She said well, I'm going
to lose my

00:31:53.900 --> 00:31:56.559
car, I'm going to lose my home and so on.
I said, well,

00:31:56.559 --> 00:31:59.320
send me your bills. Now, I don't usually do
impulsive

00:31:59.320 --> 00:32:02.580
things like that, but this had to be addressed.
So we

00:32:02.580 --> 00:32:07.460
were able to do that for her, and I mean,
that's my idea

00:32:07.460 --> 00:32:11.270
of bad luck. It's pretty high standard. And
then

00:32:11.270 --> 00:32:14.770
you'll have some dilettante calling you and
saying, "I

00:32:14.770 --> 00:32:18.809
owe $80,000 in credit cards and my husband
told me if I

00:32:18.809 --> 00:32:22.000
did this again he's going to divorce me."
And in the

00:32:22.000 --> 00:32:24.230
end we talked about things she might do. There
were

00:32:24.230 --> 00:32:27.600
some avenues to get through this. She had
a different

00:32:27.600 --> 00:32:30.130
mailbox for all the bills that came in. I
mean, she was

00:32:30.130 --> 00:32:33.650
good at this. [laughter] But it was 80,000
she had done it before

00:32:33.650 --> 00:32:36.250
as I say. Unfortunately, they were going to
build a new

00:32:36.250 --> 00:32:38.380
house -- buy a new house, and they were going
to check

00:32:38.380 --> 00:32:41.559
the credit and she was in trouble. So she
said, well,

00:32:41.559 --> 00:32:43.320
what do you think I ought to do? That I said
well --

00:32:43.320 --> 00:32:45.789
she told me that she had had a small inheritance
from --

00:32:45.789 --> 00:32:51.400
I said I'd apply that to the debt, and so
-- and then in

00:32:51.400 --> 00:32:54.419
the end she said, you mean, you aren't going
to help me?

00:32:54.419 --> 00:32:57.330
And I said no, we're not, because this doesn't
meet our

00:32:57.330 --> 00:32:58.440
criteria.
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Sure.

00:32:58.440 --> 00:33:03.330
&gt;&gt;DORIS: But those are -- they're not as -- and
then there are the crazy ones. These are always

00:33:03.330 --> 00:33:05.220
really
interesting. I heard from the Virgin Mary,

00:33:05.220 --> 00:33:08.419
folks, and
they may not have happened to any of you,

00:33:08.419 --> 00:33:09.419
and I --
[Laughing]

00:33:09.419 --> 00:33:13.040
&gt;&gt;DORIS: I'm very sad to have to tell you,
she's not a very nice person.

00:33:13.040 --> 00:33:16.090
[Laughing]
&gt;&gt;DORIS: So once in a while we get somebody

00:33:16.090 --> 00:33:19.179
that gives us a laugh. But anybody that works
--

00:33:19.179 --> 00:33:21.860
anybody that's involved in charity of this
kind is going

00:33:21.860 --> 00:33:24.310
to be having a wonderful life; I can tell
you that. And

00:33:24.310 --> 00:33:26.931
it makes changes in your own personality sometimes.
You

00:33:26.931 --> 00:33:29.309
know, they don't -- aren't quite as self-centered
and

00:33:29.309 --> 00:33:31.860
don't think they're as poor as they're putting
on.

00:33:31.860 --> 00:33:34.240
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Well, what I -- I think one of
the

00:33:34.240 --> 00:33:37.240
things that I was curious about is I'm sure
you have a

00:33:37.240 --> 00:33:40.790
lot of people ask you what it's like to have
Warren as a

00:33:40.790 --> 00:33:43.550
brother, but I --
&gt;&gt;DORIS: I can tell ya.

00:33:43.550 --> 00:33:45.740
[Laughing]
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Well, okay.

00:33:45.740 --> 00:33:47.920
&gt;&gt;DORIS: It's great.
[Laughing]

00:33:47.920 --> 00:33:50.789
&gt;&gt;DORIS: We really do have a lot in common
now

00:33:50.789 --> 00:33:54.840
and he's -- well, he urged me to write the
book; that

00:33:54.840 --> 00:33:56.940
was his idea, and --
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Did he write the forward as well?

00:33:56.940 --> 00:34:00.809
&gt;&gt;DORIS: Yeah. He wrote the forward without
reading the book. He likes the book enormously.

00:34:00.809 --> 00:34:04.800
He
sent it to everybody he knows because it's

00:34:04.800 --> 00:34:07.250
an honest
book. I mean, you could write and not tell

00:34:07.250 --> 00:34:11.840
anything
about that event in 1987, and the things that

00:34:11.840 --> 00:34:15.190
followed
it. But it wouldn't be true. It wouldn't tell

00:34:15.190 --> 00:34:17.770
the
whole thing so he admired that because a lot

00:34:17.770 --> 00:34:21.780
of people
don't do that. So it was a -- actually, it

00:34:21.780 --> 00:34:27.129
was a great
healing thing for the two of us and so -- I

00:34:27.129 --> 00:34:29.169
send him
some of the more outrageous things and some

00:34:29.169 --> 00:34:32.780
of the thank
yous. Do you know what? A lady saw that show

00:34:32.780 --> 00:34:34.540
you're
speaking of, Charlie Rose --

00:34:34.540 --> 00:34:37.909
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Mm hmm.
&gt;&gt;DORIS: -- in California, and she sent me

00:34:37.909 --> 00:34:40.230
a
letter and she said I've saved up money during

00:34:40.230 --> 00:34:43.090
my
lifetime to help other people, but she liked

00:34:43.090 --> 00:34:45.470
the way we
were doing it and and she said I'd like to

00:34:45.470 --> 00:34:49.060
give you that
savings thing. And so I thought well, we had

00:34:49.060 --> 00:34:51.119
our
lawyer -- we have a pro bono lawyer. There's

00:34:51.119 --> 00:34:53.750
some
things that go with this, kids. If they know

00:34:53.750 --> 00:34:55.250
you're
doing the right things, they want to help

00:34:55.250 --> 00:34:58.270
you. We get a
hot of things like that. But he's probably

00:34:58.270 --> 00:35:02.860
the best.
So he wrote and you have to contact the lawyer,

00:35:02.860 --> 00:35:04.500
and I
didn't think that it'd ever work out because

00:35:04.500 --> 00:35:06.390
it was
maybe just some kind of a spontaneous thing.

00:35:06.390 --> 00:35:11.119
Well, we
got a check for $187,000. So people -- you

00:35:11.119 --> 00:35:15.570
know, they may engage with you on you know
for a quarter

00:35:15.570 --> 00:35:18.240
or something, but some little act of kindness
and

00:35:18.240 --> 00:35:20.560
goodness, and then this woman -- I mean, I'm
just

00:35:20.560 --> 00:35:24.050
astounded. That was a real vote of confidence.
So we

00:35:24.050 --> 00:35:27.090
felt good about that. And we're going to put
it in some

00:35:27.090 --> 00:35:31.000
very special cause, you know.
&gt;&gt;JENNIFER: Absolutely. Well, between the

00:35:31.000 --> 00:35:33.840
Learning from Giving Foundation.
&gt;&gt;DORIS: You see, everybody feels good. The

00:35:33.840 --> 00:35:38.160
person who is empowered by what we do -- I'm
going to

00:35:38.160 --> 00:35:40.600
tell one more, and then I promise to stop.
This is one

00:35:40.600 --> 00:35:42.900
of the first ones, and it was a woman who
wrote to us

00:35:42.900 --> 00:35:45.510
from South Carolina, and she had been a nurse
in a

00:35:45.510 --> 00:35:50.790
doctor's office. This all panned out. We check
everything. And then she got arthritis and

00:35:50.790 --> 00:35:53.020
she couldn't
do it any longer. So I said, well, Willie

00:35:53.020 --> 00:35:55.780
Mae -- that
was actually her name -- Willie Mae, is there

00:35:55.780 --> 00:35:59.630
anybody
else in your home now? And she said yes, my

00:35:59.630 --> 00:36:03.000
husband,
and we always check it. It's usually a family

00:36:03.000 --> 00:36:05.630
situation. It's going to take the whole family
to pull

00:36:05.630 --> 00:36:08.520
it together. So I said well, is he working
now? She

00:36:08.520 --> 00:36:11.080
said well, no. He was driving a truck and
he didn't

00:36:11.080 --> 00:36:15.220
care for his -- you know, the route, and so
he's at home.

00:36:15.220 --> 00:36:17.830
I had visions of him sitting in a Barcalounger
at that

00:36:17.830 --> 00:36:23.380
moment. And so I said, well, tell him that
if -- when

00:36:23.380 --> 00:36:25.820
he -- if he gets a job -- when he gets a job,
